<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zachvatkin" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Edwardsiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Edwardsiana" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Edwardsiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 80 known species worldwide (
<bibRefCitation author="Dmitriev, DA" journalOrPublisher="Acta Faunistica Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" publicationUrl="http://dmitriev.speciesfile.org/" refId="B5" refString="Dmitriev, DA, 2003. 3i interactive keys and taxonomic databases. http://dmitriev.speciesfile.org/" title="3 i interactive keys and taxonomic databases." url="http://dmitriev.speciesfile.org/" year="2003">Dmitriev 2003</bibRefCitation>
), with two species having been reported from China. Here we record three more species from China and provide a key to all Chinese species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
Body cream with variable patches (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–20" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 20. Typhlocybini of China 1 - 5 dorsal view 6 - 10 head and thorax, dorsal view 11 - 15 lateral view 16 - 20 face 1, 6, 11, 16 Edwardsiana corylicola 2, 7, 12, 17 E. praedestina 3, 8, 13, 18 E. singularis 4, 9, 14, 19 Hiratettix distanti 5, 10, 15, 20 H. malaisei. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (1 - 5, 11 - 15); 0.5 mm (6 - 10, 16 - 20)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.73611.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636231" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">1-3</figureCitation>
). Crown bluntly produced, medial length shorter than distance between eyes; coronal suture distinct. Pronotum slightly wider than head (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–20" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 20. Typhlocybini of China 1 - 5 dorsal view 6 - 10 head and thorax, dorsal view 11 - 15 lateral view 16 - 20 face 1, 6, 11, 16 Edwardsiana corylicola 2, 7, 12, 17 E. praedestina 3, 8, 13, 18 E. singularis 4, 9, 14, 19 Hiratettix distanti 5, 10, 15, 20 H. malaisei. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (1 - 5, 11 - 15); 0.5 mm (6 - 10, 16 - 20)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.73611.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636231" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">6-8</figureCitation>
). Forewing with apical area short, 1/4-1/3 of total length; RP and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="MP’">MP'</normalizedToken>
petiolate or not. Hind wing with R and M confluent distally.
</paragraph>
